<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Saudi banking</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investment banking is a business of bu=
ilding long-term relationships. Your job, as an investment banker, is to be=
come close to the people who possess giant piles of money, in the hopes tha=
t one day they will do giant deals with their giant piles of money and give=
 you some of it. If you are at the weekly meeting of an investment-banking =
group and everyone is going around the room talking about what they did las=
t week, and someone says =E2=80=9CI did a billion-dollar=C2=A0merger and ea=
rned an $8=C2=A0million fee for the bank,=E2=80=9D and you say =E2=80=9CI p=
layed Settlers of Catan with Mark Zuckerberg,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<em>you win</em=
>, because the expected value of proximity to a giant pile of money is so m=
uch higher than the value of an actual fee from a normal-sized pile of mone=
y.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One result of this is that banks are alw=
ays happy to give freebies to the possessors of giant piles of money. =E2=
=80=9CWe=E2=80=99ll do this work for Facebook at no charge because the oppo=
rtunity there is so vast and we want them to owe us one.=E2=80=9D</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The possessors of giant piles of money are, often, s=
mart. Also they got to possess all of that money because they like hanging =
on to their money.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One obvious result here =
is that if you happen to possess a giant pile of money you can get free or =
discounted investment-banking services pretty much forever. You do a multib=
illion-dollar acquisition, your banker comes to you with a bill, you look a=
t her in disappointment and say =E2=80=9Ca bill? I thought we were friends,=
=E2=80=9D her heart skips with joy, she tears up the bill, she goes back to=
 her bosses and says =E2=80=9Cthe giant pile of money=C2=A0<em>thinks we=E2=
=80=99re friends</em>,=E2=80=9D her bosses congratulate her on her success =
in relationship-building, everyone is happy, and they all salivate to think=
 about how much money they=E2=80=99ll make on your=C2=A0next,=C2=A0<em>real=
ly </em>big deal. And then=C2=A0you do the next, really big deal, and you r=
epeat this process forever.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I promise you w=
ill never stop seeing <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/25093534.264700/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjEtMDktMjAvd2FsbC1zdHJlZXQtZmxvY2tlZC10by1zYXVkaS1hcmFiaWEtYnV0LXN0aWxsLW=
F3YWl0cy1mZWUtcmljaGVz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB496d5993" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> these stories=C2=A0about S=
audi Arabia</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The latest cro=
p of Saudi Arabia=E2=80=99s market newcomers is proving just as frugal when=
 it comes to paying investment bankers.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Des=
pite attracting $125 billion in orders from investors for an initial public=
 offering of Saudi Telecom Co.=E2=80=99s internet-services unit, banks incl=
uding Morgan Stanley and HSBC Holdings Plc are set to share just about $12 =
million in fees, Arabian Internet and Communications Services Co., also kno=
wn as solutions by stc, said in its prospectus.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s just 1.3% of the offering value, compared with an=
 average of about 5% or more for IPOs in the U.S. or Europe. Morgan Stanley=
 alone had a bigger payday during UiPath Inc.=E2=80=99s $1.54 billion IPO i=
n April, which generated a total of $67 million in fees. ...</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">IPO riches have yet to materialize for global banks despi=
te a bonanza of share sales this year. Wall Street heavyweights like JPMorg=
an Chase &amp; Co., Goldman Sachs Group Inc. and Citigroup Inc. have still =
flocked to the kingdom, hiring teams on the ground and sending in their top=
 executives to sway local officials in the hope of winning advisory roles.<=
/p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If banks are flocking to you b=
ecause you have so much money, you don=E2=80=99t have to give them any of i=
t.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpadd=
